                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="alberthall_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a large round concert hall in west London, which holds 8 000 people. It was built in 1868-71 in memory of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/prince-albert" title="Prince Albert definition"><span class="ndv">Prince Albert</span></a>. Various musical and sporting events take place in it, but it is best known as the concert hall where the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-proms#the_proms_topg_1" title="Proms definition"><span class="ndv">Proms</span></a> are held.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
